%section
  %h2 Note Regarding Privacy
  %p
    This data represents activity on the Libraries' public computers; activity on Library Staff
    machines is removed from ingest into MetriDoc. Usernames on public computers are used to
    map to demographic categories and for no other purpose. The data is intended to evaluate
    the products being used, the times and locations of their use, and the demographic
    categories of the user.

%hr

%section
  %h2 Introduction
  %p
    Keyserver tracks software usage on Penn Libraries public computers.
    Events and sessions are captured from Keyserver and loaded into Metridoc.
  %ul
    %li
      The
      %strong Software Usage
      page lists all managed products with checkout activity on non-staff computers,
      including status (Active / Stale / Dormant) based on days since the last checkout.
    %li
      The
      %strong Stale &amp; Dormant
      page surfaces products with no checkout in 90+ days, sorted by most dormant first.
    %li
      The
      %strong Locations
      page shows session heatmaps by hour of day and day of week, broken down by library location.
    %li
      The
      %strong By School
      page shows checkout counts per product per Alma school affiliation.
    %li
      The
      %strong By User Group
      page shows checkout counts per product per Alma user group (e.g. undergraduate, graduate, faculty).

%hr

%section
  %h2 Resources
  %h3 Database Access
  %p{:style => "padding: 0px 0px 0px 30px;"}
    For those who are connecting directly to the PostgreSQL database or who are
    using the report exporting tool, the tables for Keyserver data
    begin with the prefix "keyserver_".

  %h3 Data Tables
  %ul
    - resources.each do |resource|
      %li= link_to resource.resource_name.human, "/keyserver/#{resource.resource_name.param_key.pluralize}"

%hr

%section
  %h2 Dashboards
  %ul
    %li= link_to "Software Usage Profile", keyserver_software_usage_path
    %li= link_to "Stale & Dormant Products", keyserver_stale_path
    %li= link_to "Location Usage", keyserver_locations_path
    %li= link_to "By School", keyserver_by_school_path
    %li= link_to "By User Group", keyserver_by_user_group_path

%hr

%section
  %h2 Data Import

  %h3 File Upload
  %p
    Events and sessions data can be loaded directly through the
    = link_to "File Upload Tool", admin_tools_file_upload_imports_path
  %ol
    %li
      Export
      %code events.csv
      and/or
      %code sessions.csv
      from Keyserver.
    %li
      In the File Upload Tool, select the target table (
      %strong Keyserver Event
      or
      %strong Keyserver Session
      ) and upload the file.
    %li
      The tool accepts the raw Keyserver CSV export as-is — abbreviated column headers (e.g.
      %code name
      ,
      %code user
      ,
      %code event
      ) are mapped to database columns automatically.
    %li Duplicate records are handled on the backend; re-uploading a file that has already been imported is safe.

  %h3 Rake Import
  %p
    To load data via the command line, export
    %code events.csv
    and
    %code sessions.csv
    from Keyserver into
    %code /tmp/keyserver/
    then run:
  %pre rake import -- --config_folder keyserver
